# .cursorrules — QRS

These rules are always active. Follow them without being asked.

---

## Stack Constraints

- Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript. No Pages Router.
- Tailwind CSS for all styling. No CSS modules, no styled-components, no inline style objects unless unavoidable.
- shadcn/ui for dashboard/admin UI. Custom components for shop UI.
- Prisma 5 + Neon (Postgres). No raw SQL unless Prisma cannot express the query.
- Clerk for auth. No NextAuth, no custom auth.
- Resend for email. No Nodemailer, no SendGrid.
- Anthropic SDK for AI features. No OpenAI.

---

## File Structure

```
src/
  app/
    page.tsx                    # Marketing landing
    layout.tsx                  # Root layout with ClerkProvider
    sign-up/[[...sign-up]]/     # Clerk signup
    sign-in/[[...sign-in]]/     # Clerk signin
    onboarding/page.tsx         # Post-signup onboarding wizard
    dashboard/                  # Seller admin (protected)
      page.tsx
      settings/page.tsx
    [slug]/                     # Public shop (unprotected)
      page.tsx
      success/page.tsx
    api/
      webhooks/
        stripe/route.ts
        telegram/route.ts
      cron/
        reset-order-counts/route.ts
  components/
    shop/                       # Swipe UI components
    dashboard/                  # Admin/dashboard components
    onboarding/                 # Onboarding wizard components
    ui/                         # shadcn/ui components
  lib/
    stripe.ts                   # Per-seller Stripe client factory
    resend.ts                   # Email fulfillment
    telegram.ts                 # Telegram utilities (per-seller)
    ai-analysis.ts              # Claude Vision
    fulfillment.ts              # Fulfillment router
    seller.ts                   # Seller lookup helpers
  middleware.ts
prisma/
  schema.prisma
```

---

## Multi-Tenancy Rules

- Every DB query that touches Products, HeroImages, or Orders MUST filter by `sellerId`.
- Never query across sellers. No query without a `where: { sellerId }` clause on tenant-scoped tables.
- Get `sellerId` from the Clerk session → Seller record lookup. Never trust a `sellerId` from the client.
- The seller lookup helper lives in `src/lib/seller.ts`. Use it everywhere. Do not inline the lookup.

---

## Auth Rules

- `/dashboard` and all sub-routes are protected by Clerk middleware.
- `/[slug]` and `/api/webhooks/*` are public.
- Post-signup: if authenticated user has no Seller record, redirect to `/onboarding`.
- Never expose Stripe keys, Shippo keys, or Telegram tokens in API responses or client bundles.

---

## Approval Rule

Never execute fixes or make changes without first explaining the problem and what the fix would do, then waiting for explicit approval. Diagnose first, act second.

If a task is ambiguous, stop and ask. Do not assume and proceed.

---

## TypeScript Rules

- No `any`. Use proper types or `unknown` with a type guard.
- All API route handlers must type their request and response.
- Prisma-generated types are the source of truth for DB models. Do not re-declare them.

---

## Component Rules

- Server Components by default. Add `"use client"` only when needed (event handlers, hooks, browser APIs).
- No prop drilling more than 2 levels. Use context or pass data at the page level.
- Every async component and data fetch has a loading state and an error state.

---

## Naming Conventions

- Files: kebab-case (`swipe-card.tsx`, `seller-settings.tsx`)
- Components: PascalCase (`SwipeCard`, `SellerSettings`)
- API routes: follow Next.js convention (`route.ts`)
- DB fields: camelCase (Prisma default)
- Environment variables: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

---

## What Not to Do

- Do not install new dependencies without flagging them first.
- Do not add new color tokens, fonts, or design system elements without explicit instruction.
- Do not change the swipe gesture mapping (right=buy, left=skip, up=save).
- Do not remove the `e.stopPropagation()` from action button handlers.
- Do not auto-set product prices from AI. AI suggests, seller confirms.
- Do not expose seller Stripe keys in any client-side code or API response.
- Do not create new API routes for operations Prisma can handle in a Server Action or Server Component.
- Do not run `git commit` without explicit approval.
- Do not run `git push` without explicit approval.
- Do not use the GitHub API to create, edit, or delete files.
- All file changes must be made to the local filesystem only.
- Never write directly to the remote repository.
---

*QRS — .cursorrules — June 2026*
